OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,FThe mother of a nine-year-old boy who
OL,7,F"died in agony" after botched surgery
OL,8,Fexclusively tells ITV News of her
OL,9,Fshock at finding out that a surgeon
OL,10,Fcaused "fatal harm" to her son over 10
OL,11,Fyears ago, as ITV News Correspondent
OL,12,FRachel Townsend reports
OL,14,FWords by Rachel Townsend, ITV News
OL,15,FCorrespondent, produced by Eleanor
OL,16,FGregory, Senior Producer, and edited
OL,17,Fby Jake Langtree, Camera Operator
OL,19,FFor a decade, Elizabeth Moate has been
OL,20,Fdealing with the death of her nine-
OL,21,Fyear-old son, Jack.
OL,26,@rD@HOUrD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
