OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,FSitting with her, it is clear it has
OL,7,Fbeen unbearable for her. "The best you
OL,8,Fcan hope for" she says, "is to learn
OL,9,Fhow to live with the pain."
OL,11,FIn January this year, while trying to
OL,12,Flive with that pain, she was contacted
OL,13,Fby Addenbrooke's Hospital in Cambridge
OL,14,F- where Jack had been treated - and
OL,15,Fasked to come in for a meeting with
OL,16,Fthe Chief Medical Officer.
OL,26,@oD@ZOUpD@MO]pD@YOUqD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,FShe went alone, believing nothing
OL,7,Fcould be worse than hearing about her
OL,8,Fson's death. But within just a few
OL,9,Fminutes, her world came crashing down,
OL,10,Fonce again.
OL,12,FElizabeth was told that Jack had
OL,13,Fsuffered "fatal physical harm" during
OL,14,Fsurgery at the hospital weeks before
OL,15,Fhis death. And so, her son hadn't died
OL,16,Fof natural causes as she was
OL,17,Foriginally told. His case is now with
OL,18,Fthe coroner.
OL,26,@uD@JOUuD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,F"It destroyed me. To sit there and be
OL,7,Ftold in a room that your son has had a
OL,8,Ffatal outcome from surgery, I just
OL,9,Fwasn't expecting the news to be as
OL,10,Fhorrific as it was.
OL,12,F"Every single day, I relive everything
OL,13,Fand think of all the opportunities
OL,14,FAddenbrooke's had to save his life and
OL,15,Fchose not to. So many chances to save
OL,16,Fhis life and do things differently.
OL,17,FAnd since then I've had no answers
OL,18,Feither."
OL,26,@nD@AOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,FAnd there were missed chances. A month
OL,7,Fafter Jack's original surgery, which
OL,8,Fwas supposed to improve his mobility,
OL,9,FJack was still in enormous amounts of
OL,10,Fpain. Elizabeth took him back to
OL,11,Fhospital and only then was he X-rayed.
OL,12,FDespite it showing bones out of place,
OL,13,Fhe was discharged by Dr Stohr.
OL,15,F"The X-ray was clear as day that
OL,16,Fsomething was wrong and yet nothing
OL,17,Fwas done. It's bad enough that the
OL,18,Foperation didn't go well... and then
OL,19,Fbring him back and just to send him
OL,20,Fhome to die.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,F"He was still in absolute agony, and
OL,7,Fno matter how many times I reached out
OL,8,FI was told to trust the process, he's
OL,9,Fhealing fine. But as we know he wasn't
OL,10,Ffine and he never stood a chance."
OL,12,FWe now know that there were 32 missed
OL,13,Fopportunities to intervene in Dr
OL,14,FStohr's practice. None were taken and
OL,15,Fso after, Jack's death, Dr Stohr went
OL,16,Fon to operate on hundreds more
OL,17,Fchildren.
OL,26,@rD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,FElizabeth Maliakal , a lawyer
OL,7,Frepresenting many of their families
OL,8,Fbelieves the trust's failure to act is
OL,9,Finexcusable.
OL,11,F"It's wrongdoing at every level. It's
OL,12,Fwrongdoing from the surgeon herself,
OL,13,Fit's wrongdoing from the people that
OL,14,Fmanage the surgeon, from the people
OL,15,Fwho manage the surgeon," she told ITV
OL,16,FNews.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,F"It's wrongdoing from the department,
OL,7,Ffrom the clinical division, the trust
OL,8,Fboard and the management of the trust,
OL,9,Fso it's a failure at absolutely every
OL,10,Flevel, and they've failed the patients
OL,11,Foperated on by this individual surgeon
OL,12,Fwho have come to harm."
OL,14,FWith enormous sadness etched across
OL,15,Fher face, Jack's mum sits calmly,
OL,16,Ftelling me about the years with Jack
OL,17,Fshe has missed out on.
OL,26,@tD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1772737884
OL,3,CFamily of boy who 'died in agony'
OL,4,Cspeak of 'fatal harm' caused in surgery
OL,6,F"I've lost my 9 year old son. That
OL,7,Fcan't change and I'm never going to
OL,8,Fget those years back and so
OL,9,Faccountability needs to happen."
OL,11,FAccountability, in her eyes means Dr
OL,12,FStohr is struck off the Medical
OL,13,FRegister. At present she is only
OL,14,Fsuspended by Cambridge University
OL,15,FHospital Foundation Trust and is still
OL,16,Fbeing paid.
OL,18,FDr Stohr has previously told us that
OL,19,Fshe always strives to provide the
OL,20,Fhighest standards of care to her
OL,21,Fpatients.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
